      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is a pretty aggressive auto-fetch interval. The shortest interval supported by \"git maintenance\" is hourly. If this feature is used by many developers it can potentially generate a lot of traffic for git servers. The values supported by `git maintenance` tasks are `hourly, daily, weekly`. Maybe the interval should be made configurable.\n\nI think this auto-fetch should also honour the git option \"remote.\u003cname\u003e.skipFetchAll\" which is used by `git maintenance prefetch`.\nSee https://git-scm.com/docs/git-maintenance#Documentation/git-maintenance.txt-prefetch.\nThis would provide a way to disable auto-fetch for selected remotes.\nThis enhancement can be implemented in another change.",
